  "title": "Director, Credit – Infrastructure & Project Finance (Asia Pacific)",
  "description": "<p>A reputable international bank is seeking a senior credit officer to assess and manage risk for project and structured finance transactions across renewables, energy, digital infrastructure, transportation, and broader infrastructure markets in APAC.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Independently review complex credit proposals and deliver clear, concise risk assessments.</li><li>Analyse borrowers, sponsors, and project structures; recommend credit strategies aligned with risk appetite.</li><li>Monitor portfolio exposures, identify emerging risks, and develop mitigation plans.</li><li>Perform portfolio analytics across markets, sectors, and products to support risk oversight.</li><li>Guide business units on deal structuring, credit terms, and policy alignment.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>7–10+ years’ experience in credit or risk, ideally in project finance or infrastructure.</li><li>Strong analytical skills with ability to explain complex financing risks clearly.</li><li>Excellent communication, Excel proficiency, and strong interest in APAC energy and infrastructure.</li></ul><p>Reg No. R1875901<br />BeathChapman Pte Ltd<br />Licence no. 16S8112</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 7,
